  "title": "Trade Compliance Officer",
  "description": "<p><strong>About Company:</strong></p><p>Established in 1978, our client is a market leader in precision measuring instruments with network of subsidiaries in Malaysia, Thailand, Indonesia and Vietnam. They offer a comprehensive range of equipment and services such as Coordinate Measuring Machines, Vision Measuring Systems, and more.</p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>- Review and assessment of transactions and product shifting applications and any related impact</p><p>- Classification of product based on export control policies (e.g., strategic & non-strategic products)</p><p>- Collaborating with HQ to ensure updated information on policies and whereabouts of equipment's are updated into the Company's database</p><p>- Ensuring that the Trade Control department operations are in accordance with government laws & regulations as well the global control policy for the Company brand</p><p>- Management and ensuring appropriate record keeping of documents relating to the Trade Control department and its related operations</p><p>- Perform screening of end-users of the Company’s product before shipment or quotation</p><p>- Provide training support on the importance of compliance in exports to the Group and custom related matters</p><p>- Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned</p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>- Experience in either Product Classification, Customs Regulations or Singapore Strategic Goods Control Act</p><p>- Diploma/Degree in relevant course of study</p><p>- A good team player with strong interpersonal skills</p><p><strong>Compensation:</strong></p><p>- Working location: Kallang</p><p>- Working hours: 9am to 5pm</p><p>- AWS</p><p>- Claimable transport allowance</p><p>- Opportunities for personal/career development</p><p>- Competitive medical coverage<a href=\"https://www.jointhire.com.sg/job/3560?utm_source=followup\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"></a></p>",
